The process whereby the accused and the prosecutor in a criminal case work out a mutually satisfactory disposition of the case subject to court approval. It usually involves the defendant's pleading guilty to a lesser offense or to only one or some of the counts of a multicount indictment in return for a lighter sentence than that possible for the graver charge. 

Source: [VA Circuit Court Criminal Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_criminal/glossary.pdf)